### 4.3 Ingest SMS

**POST** `/mobile/tenants/{tenant}/banking/ingest/sms`
**Auth:** Required
**Permission:** `transactions.import`

Submits raw SMS text from a bank alert. The system parses the transaction details (amount, type, date, reference, party name) using an AI SMS parser, runs it through the narration pipeline, and creates a `BankTransaction` record for review.

Duplicate transactions (same bank reference within the tenant) are silently deduplicated — no error is returned.

**Request body:**

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `raw_sms` | string | Yes | Full raw SMS text from the bank (min 10, max 1000 chars) |
| `bank_account_name` | string | No | Label for the source account (e.g. `"HDFC Savings"`) |

```json
{
  "raw_sms": "Dear Customer, INR 5,000.00 credited to your A/C XX1234 on 13-04-26 by NEFT from ACME CORP LTD. Ref No: NEFT123456. Avl Bal: INR 45,230.00",
  "bank_account_name": "HDFC Savings"
}
```

**Response — 200 OK:**

```json
{
  "message": "SMS processed and transaction added for review."
}
```

**Error responses:**

| Status | Reason |
|---|---|
| 422 | Validation failed (empty/too-short SMS) |
| 403 | Missing `transactions.import` permission |

