### 4.7 Correct Transaction

**POST** `/mobile/tenants/{tenant}/banking/transactions/{transaction}/correct`
**Auth:** Required
**Permission:** `transactions.edit`

Re-categorises a transaction with a new head/sub-head, optionally saves the correction as a learned rule for future transactions, and optionally reconciles it against an invoice.

This is the most powerful review action — use it when the AI suggestion is wrong or incomplete.

**Path params:**

| Param | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `transaction` | integer | Transaction ID from the pending list |

**Request body:**

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `narration_head_id` | integer | Yes | ID of the narration head to assign |
| `narration_sub_head_id` | integer | No | ID of the sub-head to assign |
| `narration_note` | string | No | Human-readable note for this transaction (max 500 chars) |
| `party_name` | string | No | Counterparty name (max 255 chars). Required if the chosen sub-head has `requires_party: true` |
| `save_as_rule` | boolean | No | If `true`, saves this correction as a learned rule so future similar transactions are auto-categorised. Default: `false` |
| `invoice_id` | integer | No | Reconcile this transaction against an invoice by its ID |
| `invoice_number` | string | No | Reconcile by invoice number (alternative to `invoice_id`) |
| `unreconcile` | boolean | No | If `true`, removes an existing reconciliation link. Default: `false` |

**Minimal example (re-categorise only):**

```json
{
  "narration_head_id": 2,
  "narration_sub_head_id": 10,
  "narration_note": "Monthly office rent"
}
```

**Full example (re-categorise + save rule + reconcile):**

```json
{
  "narration_head_id": 1,
  "narration_sub_head_id": 2,
  "party_name": "Acme Corp",
  "narration_note": "Consulting retainer from Acme Corp",
  "save_as_rule": true,
  "invoice_id": 42
}
```

**Response — 200 OK:**

```json
{
  "message": "Transaction corrected."
}
```

**Error responses:**

| Status | Reason |
|---|---|
| 403 | Missing `transactions.edit` permission, or transaction belongs to a different tenant |
| 404 | Transaction not found in this tenant |
| 422 | Validation failed — e.g. missing `narration_head_id`, non-existent IDs, or reconciling an invoice from a different tenant |

**Learned rule behaviour:**
When `save_as_rule: true`, the system creates a `NarrationRule` scoped to this tenant. The match value is derived from the `party_name` (preferred), bank reference tokens, or raw narration words. The `narration_note` is templatised — actual amounts, dates, and party names are replaced with `{amount}`, `{date}`, `{party}` placeholders so future matches get accurate dynamic notes.

